e expectancy, and how women are affected economically while men are affected socially. With a realistic yet passionate voice, Crowley shares the personal positive outlooks and the necessary supportive public policies that must be enacted to best help the newly divorced. Engaging and instructive, Gray Divorce is a must-read for anyone interested in contemporary American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDivorcezUnited States. 0aOlder peoplezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh1 aWeiner, Marc D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096811040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520968110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520968110/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles